<item>
            <title>[SPARK-10351] UnsafeRow.getUTF8String should handle off-heap backed UnsafeRow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10351</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;UnsafeRow.getUTF8String&lt;/tt&gt; delegates to &lt;tt&gt;UTF8String.fromAddress&lt;/tt&gt; which returns &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; when passed a &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; base object, failing to handle off-heap backed {{UnsafeRow}}s correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will also cause a &lt;tt&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/tt&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;getString&lt;/tt&gt; is called with off-heap storage.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12860530">SPARK-10351</key>
